1
00:01:01,061 --> 00:01:03,438
THIS DRAMA IS PURELY FICTIONAL
AND IS NOT ASSOCIATED WITH

2
00:01:03,521 --> 00:01:05,982
ACTUAL PEOPLE, PARTIES, LOCATIONS,
CORPORATIONS OR INCIDENTS

3
00:01:17,786 --> 00:01:19,496
That footage won't be disclosed.

4
00:01:20,080 --> 00:01:20,955
Why not?

5
00:01:23,666 --> 00:01:24,918
It'll be hard to determine

6
00:01:25,001 --> 00:01:27,045
the cause of the accident
with the footage alone.

7
00:01:27,128 --> 00:01:30,423
And even if we disclose it now,
it'll end up getting buried.

8
00:01:30,507 --> 00:01:33,259
Mr. Song and Mr. Lee are very close.

9
00:01:33,343 --> 00:01:35,804
Mr. Song will soon be appointed
Minister of Justice.

10
00:01:35,887 --> 00:01:39,599
Then he'll do whatever it takes
to pressure the police and prosecution.

11
00:01:39,682 --> 00:01:41,601
But that accident cost someone's life.

12
00:01:42,102 --> 00:01:44,020
Are you saying
we should turn a blind eye to it?

13
00:01:44,104 --> 00:01:45,647
No, something will be done.

14
00:01:45,730 --> 00:01:49,651
But Mr. Jang made the best choice
he could've made.

15
00:01:49,859 --> 00:01:52,737
Unless the law and the system change,
nothing can be done.

16
00:01:52,821 --> 00:01:56,282
And Mr. Jang is trying to change them.

17
00:02:00,870 --> 00:02:04,624
I don't believe
that you've made the best choice.

18
00:02:09,170 --> 00:02:10,088
What's your point?

19
00:02:11,673 --> 00:02:13,216
I don't know much about politics.

20
00:02:13,591 --> 00:02:14,759
But

21
00:02:16,886 --> 00:02:18,054
I don't think this is right.

22
00:02:18,638 --> 00:02:20,557
How could you change the world

23
00:02:20,640 --> 00:02:22,433
when you disregard someone's life?

24
00:02:24,686 --> 00:02:27,021
When did it start going south?

25
00:02:27,647 --> 00:02:31,192
Don't trust Mr. Song and Mr. Lee too much.

26
00:02:31,276 --> 00:02:33,361
They'll ditch you when you become useless.

27
00:02:33,444 --> 00:02:34,654
I know.

28
00:02:34,737 --> 00:02:36,406
And I'm just using them as well.

29
00:02:38,908 --> 00:02:41,161
Take a good look at yourself now.

30
00:02:41,995 --> 00:02:43,454
Who is the one that's being used?

31
00:02:43,538 --> 00:02:45,874
If you're planning to help
Assemblyman Lee, just give up.

32
00:02:46,457 --> 00:02:47,834
What if I stop you?

33
00:02:50,295 --> 00:02:51,296
What will you do then?

34
00:02:53,339 --> 00:02:56,593
Mutual interests formed
by misunderstandings and conflicts.

35
00:02:57,510 --> 00:03:01,806
Life is entangled
like a messy skein of thread.

36
00:03:03,725 --> 00:03:04,726
Tae-jun.

37
00:03:04,976 --> 00:03:07,437
Don't get intoxicated
with what Mr. Lee has to offer.

38
00:03:24,454 --> 00:03:26,206
A tangled skein of thread.

39
00:03:26,289 --> 00:03:27,832
If you're going to fight with someone,

40
00:03:28,333 --> 00:03:30,752
you must win at all costs.

41
00:03:33,379 --> 00:03:35,673
I'll help you. Let's fight together.

42
00:03:39,719 --> 00:03:41,846
Are you really going to keep fighting
till the end?

43
00:03:43,306 --> 00:03:45,141
-Are you?
-I need to see the fight through.

44
00:03:45,225 --> 00:03:47,435
When Mr. Song is appointed
Minister of Justice,

45
00:03:47,518 --> 00:03:50,355
he'll gain authority to command
the entire prosecution service.

46
00:03:50,438 --> 00:03:52,148
That won't happen.

47
00:03:56,152 --> 00:03:57,779
Mr. Song...

48
00:03:59,322 --> 00:04:01,199
won't be appointed as a minister.

49
00:04:04,244 --> 00:04:06,287
Independent assemblyman,
Mr. Lee Seong-min,

50
00:04:06,371 --> 00:04:08,414
is joining
the Legislation and Judiciary Committee.

51
00:04:08,498 --> 00:04:11,626
Assemblyman Jang Yong-gi
resigned from the committee,

52
00:04:11,709 --> 00:04:14,671
and Assemblyman Lee, who is now
on the Environment and Labor Committee,

53
00:04:14,754 --> 00:04:16,839
will be taking his seat.

54
00:04:19,008 --> 00:04:21,761
The more you try to untangle
the knotted skein of thread,

55
00:04:24,138 --> 00:04:26,933
you won't be able to find the knot,
and it'll get tangled up even more.

56
00:04:28,017 --> 00:04:29,560
In the end, the skein will be messier.

57
00:04:38,319 --> 00:04:41,406
EPISODE 7

58
00:04:51,082 --> 00:04:52,041
What's wrong with this?

59
00:04:55,086 --> 00:04:57,630
Damn it. What's wrong now?

60
00:04:57,755 --> 00:04:59,173
Where did I put the scissors?

61
00:04:59,632 --> 00:05:01,259
Where are my scissors?

62
00:05:05,555 --> 00:05:06,389
Did I see that right?

63
00:05:11,853 --> 00:05:12,687
KIM MYEONG-SU

64
00:05:12,770 --> 00:05:15,565
I searched this place upside down
for this. Why is this here?

65
00:05:16,899 --> 00:05:17,817
Unbelievable.

66
00:05:26,451 --> 00:05:27,785
Gosh, where's my pass?

67
00:05:29,078 --> 00:05:30,330
This is driving me crazy.

68
00:05:34,459 --> 00:05:36,127
-What are you looking for?
-What?

69
00:05:37,920 --> 00:05:39,005
It's nothing.

70
00:05:39,589 --> 00:05:40,423
What is it?

71
00:05:43,593 --> 00:05:45,553
You wore this suit, didn't you?

72
00:05:48,806 --> 00:05:51,392
Well, Mom. Let me explain.

73
00:05:52,560 --> 00:05:55,772
Remember Dong-su?
I had to wear it to Dong-su's wedding.

74
00:05:56,022 --> 00:05:57,398
-To the wedding?
-Yes.

75
00:05:57,482 --> 00:05:58,608
Is that so?

76
00:05:59,192 --> 00:06:00,109
Wait, Mom.

77
00:06:00,360 --> 00:06:01,194
Hands off.

78
00:06:01,861 --> 00:06:02,820
Let go!

79
00:06:08,993 --> 00:06:09,827
HAN DO-GYEONG

80
00:06:13,831 --> 00:06:15,333
What are you up to these days?

81
00:06:16,042 --> 00:06:17,043
Mom, it's...

82
00:06:17,126 --> 00:06:20,004
It's been a month since
you stopped going to your classes.

83
00:06:20,588 --> 00:06:21,881
I called your school.

84
00:06:23,174 --> 00:06:25,468
What on earth are you doing these days?

85
00:06:26,719 --> 00:06:27,929
Explain this. What is this?

86
00:06:30,139 --> 00:06:32,517
Well, I've been going
to the National Assembly.

87
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:34,143
What? National Assembly?

88
00:06:34,227 --> 00:06:35,686
Why would you go there?

89
00:06:35,978 --> 00:06:39,065
I've been working at an assemblyman's
office to become a chief of staff.

90
00:06:39,649 --> 00:06:40,733
Chief of staff?

91
00:06:41,734 --> 00:06:43,861
You brat.
I supported you to be a civil servant.

92
00:06:44,362 --> 00:06:46,781
-How could you pull a stunt like this?
-Wait, wait.

93
00:06:48,032 --> 00:06:49,325
They are civil servants too.

94
00:06:50,368 --> 00:06:51,702
-They are?
-Yes.

95
00:06:52,745 --> 00:06:53,579
Look.

96
00:06:54,664 --> 00:06:56,374
It says so here. Can you see?

97
00:06:56,624 --> 00:06:59,127
So are you telling me
that you're a civil servant?

98
00:07:00,002 --> 00:07:02,713
No, I'm just an intern now.

99
00:07:02,797 --> 00:07:04,298
But if I keep working, I'll become one.

100
00:07:04,382 --> 00:07:06,384
If I do, it'll be
a privileged government position.

101
00:07:06,467 --> 00:07:07,885
What's that?

102
00:07:08,886 --> 00:07:09,929
Well...

103
00:07:11,347 --> 00:07:12,807
It's a special position.

104
00:07:13,474 --> 00:07:14,767
A special position?

105
00:07:15,685 --> 00:07:17,270
Is it some kind of specialized position?

106
00:07:18,980 --> 00:07:22,400
Well, I guess you can say that.
It is special.

107
00:07:27,447 --> 00:07:30,074
Mom, I'm late.

108
00:07:30,700 --> 00:07:31,951
I'll tell you in detail tonight.

109
00:07:32,452 --> 00:07:33,744
I'm sorry.

110
00:07:34,412 --> 00:07:35,580
Hey, Do-gyeong.

111
00:07:38,166 --> 00:07:40,209
Lee Chang-jin,
the CEO of Joojin Constructions,

112
00:07:40,293 --> 00:07:41,836
visited the family of Mr. Yu Jin-su,

113
00:07:41,919 --> 00:07:44,964
who lost his life in the conveyor belt
accident at the cement factory,

114
00:07:45,047 --> 00:07:47,049
and apologized on his knees.

115
00:07:47,133 --> 00:07:50,595
He stated that he'd cooperate
with the police investigation...

116
00:07:50,720 --> 00:07:52,138
I don't know much about politics.

117
00:07:52,722 --> 00:07:53,639
But

118
00:07:56,017 --> 00:07:57,226
I don't think this is right.

119
00:07:57,810 --> 00:07:59,729
How could you change the world

120
00:08:00,313 --> 00:08:01,772
when you disregard someone's life?

121
00:08:03,858 --> 00:08:06,736
Why did I do that? It's not like
I know anything about politics.

122
00:08:11,073 --> 00:08:12,283
MR. OH

123
00:08:14,368 --> 00:08:15,369
Yes, Mr. Oh.

124
00:08:18,247 --> 00:08:19,332
Goodness.

125
00:08:20,833 --> 00:08:21,751
Come in.

126
00:08:24,462 --> 00:08:25,922
It's the schedule for the hearing.

127
00:08:29,300 --> 00:08:30,134
HEARING SCHEDULE

128
00:08:30,259 --> 00:08:32,220
ASSEMBLYMAN LEE SEONG-MIN

129
00:08:42,396 --> 00:08:45,107
How could they replace the panel
when the hearing is around the corner?

130
00:08:45,191 --> 00:08:47,485
Even if Chairperson Lee approved,
this isn't appropriate.

131
00:08:48,069 --> 00:08:50,947
Mr. Song, you should go to Chairperson Lee
and make a complaint.

132
00:08:51,030 --> 00:08:53,366
I'll round up the members
of our party and their staff.

133
00:08:54,158 --> 00:08:55,493
If you meet with him now,

134
00:08:55,576 --> 00:08:57,578
it might seem as if
you are exerting pressure.

135
00:08:57,662 --> 00:09:00,081
That will only attract attention
to your hearing.

136
00:09:01,958 --> 00:09:04,919
I doubt that this plan was concocted
from small fry like him.

137
00:09:05,002 --> 00:09:06,462
Is it Kang Seon-yeong again?

138
00:09:07,421 --> 00:09:08,506
Goodness.

139
00:09:08,589 --> 00:09:10,716
I shouldn't have stirred up
a hornet's nest.

140
00:09:10,800 --> 00:09:13,427
-Seriously. You're of no use.
-Sir...

141
00:09:13,553 --> 00:09:14,387
Damn it.

142
00:09:21,936 --> 00:09:23,479
CHIEF PRESIDENTIAL SECRETARY

143
00:09:25,439 --> 00:09:27,900
There's never a quiet day
in our office, is there?

144
00:09:30,194 --> 00:09:31,612
Goodness.

145
00:09:35,575 --> 00:09:38,452
You didn't plot this
with Ms. Kang again, did you?

146
00:09:42,123 --> 00:09:43,040
I asked just in case.

147
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:45,376
Look at how your face changed.

148
00:09:46,794 --> 00:09:48,045
Goodness.

149
00:09:48,629 --> 00:09:50,631
-Mr. Han isn't here yet?
-No.

150
00:09:51,132 --> 00:09:52,508
How could an intern be late?

151
00:09:52,592 --> 00:09:54,927
I sent him on an errand for something.

152
00:09:57,888 --> 00:10:00,224
What? I can't send an intern on an errand?

153
00:10:03,060 --> 00:10:04,061
You're all glaring at me.

154
00:10:06,564 --> 00:10:07,607
Let's go.

155
00:10:07,690 --> 00:10:08,858
-Yes, sir.
-Have a good day.

156
00:10:08,941 --> 00:10:09,775
Have a good day, sir.

157
00:10:12,486 --> 00:10:14,280
-Jong-uk.
-Yes?

158
00:10:17,325 --> 00:10:19,827
Give me the list of members
of our party in Seongjin City.

159
00:10:19,910 --> 00:10:22,038
Seongjin City? Hold on.

160
00:10:26,834 --> 00:10:28,336
LIST OF PARTY MEMBERS IN SEONGJIN

161
00:10:28,919 --> 00:10:30,588
Why do you need the list?

162
00:10:30,671 --> 00:10:32,465
Because I'm grateful to them.

163
00:10:37,887 --> 00:10:39,597
JANG CHUN-BAE
DAEHAN PARTY

164
00:10:55,613 --> 00:10:57,406
The doors are closing.

165
00:11:01,661 --> 00:11:04,372
Ms. Kang, I'd like
to offer my advice to you.

166
00:11:05,373 --> 00:11:09,210
If you switch sides whenever
you get a chance, you won't survive here.

167
00:11:10,503 --> 00:11:13,005
You must make your move
after securing your spot.

168
00:11:13,089 --> 00:11:15,466
You only play with fire
when you don't know any better.

169
00:11:16,384 --> 00:11:17,468
Thank you for your advice.

170
00:11:18,761 --> 00:11:19,804
But it's too late.

171
00:11:19,887 --> 00:11:22,264
I plan to play with a bigger fire now.

172
00:11:32,650 --> 00:11:34,694
You're joining the Judiciary Committee
at a crucial moment.

173
00:11:34,777 --> 00:11:37,279
-How does it feel?
-I'm a bit dazed.

174
00:11:37,363 --> 00:11:39,073
As a newly appointed member
of the committee,

175
00:11:39,156 --> 00:11:42,535
I must do my due diligence
not to harm the other assembly members.

176
00:11:42,618 --> 00:11:45,371
What will you be focusing on
at Assemblyman Song's hearing?

177
00:11:45,454 --> 00:11:46,914
The Minister of Justice

178
00:11:46,997 --> 00:11:49,750
must impartially establish law and order.

179
00:11:49,834 --> 00:11:51,877
The Minister's role
is very important in our society

180
00:11:51,961 --> 00:11:54,588
as he must uphold the human rights
and supervise the prosecution.

181
00:11:55,172 --> 00:11:57,258
Therefore, this position
demands higher standards

182
00:11:57,341 --> 00:12:00,845
in terms of obeying the law and ethics
compared to other Cabinet Members.

183
00:12:03,681 --> 00:12:07,643
I plan to verify and weigh
if the nominee, Assemblyman Song,

184
00:12:07,727 --> 00:12:09,353
indeed carries such traits

185
00:12:09,687 --> 00:12:11,856
from the perspectives of the people.

186
00:12:14,859 --> 00:12:15,943
Things are bustling here.

187
00:12:16,527 --> 00:12:18,904
Yes, it should be
for a happy occasion like today.

188
00:12:18,988 --> 00:12:20,156
You have a point,

189
00:12:20,239 --> 00:12:22,491
but it's too soon to tell

190
00:12:22,575 --> 00:12:24,744
if this will be a happy occasion
or a tragic one.

191
00:12:25,369 --> 00:12:27,288
Prepare for your happy occasion well.

192
00:12:27,788 --> 00:12:29,582
I want to enjoy it too.

193
00:12:34,086 --> 00:12:35,087
Hey, Ms. Kang.

194
00:12:38,340 --> 00:12:39,842
Are you heading to Jungil-gu?

195
00:12:40,384 --> 00:12:41,927
-Yes.
-Do your best.

196
00:12:42,011 --> 00:12:44,180
You must maintain
a good relationship with the mayor.

197
00:12:44,263 --> 00:12:45,806
That will help you gain more votes.

198
00:12:48,184 --> 00:12:51,729
By the way, don't forget to add my name
to your lone-parent support project.

199
00:12:52,438 --> 00:12:54,190
Okay, I will.

200
00:13:02,823 --> 00:13:05,743
Don't you think you're being
too generous with Ms. Kang?

201
00:13:05,826 --> 00:13:08,162
You never know when she's going
to stab us in the back again.

202
00:13:08,788 --> 00:13:11,791
She's more than capable of doing so.

203
00:13:11,874 --> 00:13:13,584
Put a tail on her.

204
00:13:14,168 --> 00:13:15,002
Yes, sir.

205
00:13:15,085 --> 00:13:17,880
We must keep a stronger grip on her
when she's trapped,

206
00:13:17,963 --> 00:13:19,340
so she doesn't try to resist.

207
00:13:23,719 --> 00:13:27,139
The committee seems to be going through
a rough patch. Will that affect you?

208
00:13:28,349 --> 00:13:31,685
As you know, there are always arguments
and biting remarks at hearings like this.

209
00:13:31,811 --> 00:13:33,979
If the hearing progress report
isn't approved,

210
00:13:34,063 --> 00:13:36,190
it'll impose a great deal
of pressure on the Blue House.

211
00:13:36,273 --> 00:13:38,484
As the former minister stepped down,

212
00:13:38,567 --> 00:13:42,404
the President is even considering
to withdraw the minister appointment.

213
00:13:44,281 --> 00:13:46,951
Please make sure the President
doesn't have to make that choice.

214
00:13:48,494 --> 00:13:51,497
Please don't worry.
That should never happen.

215
00:13:52,122 --> 00:13:54,375
Of course. Please have your tea.

216
00:13:54,750 --> 00:13:55,751
Have your tea.

217
00:14:04,718 --> 00:14:06,554
-I'll see you soon.
-Goodbye.

218
00:14:13,519 --> 00:14:16,522
Damn it. That troublemaker, Lee Seong-min.

219
00:14:16,605 --> 00:14:19,900
He has nothing to lose,
but he can be such a hassle.

220
00:14:20,234 --> 00:14:22,820
Call up Lee Seong-min
and invite him out for a meal.

221
00:14:24,947 --> 00:14:26,323
What do you plan on doing?

222
00:14:26,991 --> 00:14:28,492
He doesn't have ambition,

223
00:14:28,576 --> 00:14:30,327
so I'll make him ambitious.

224
00:14:32,246 --> 00:14:33,497
Goodness.

225
00:14:38,085 --> 00:14:40,212
CONFERENCE ROOM

226
00:14:40,796 --> 00:14:43,007
I'd like your support
for the lone-parent support project,

227
00:14:43,090 --> 00:14:44,425
so it runs smoothly.

228
00:14:44,508 --> 00:14:46,760
Of course.
I'm looking forward to working with you.

229
00:14:49,054 --> 00:14:50,055
Let's go back in.

230
00:14:53,100 --> 00:14:54,602
Did the meeting go well?

231
00:14:55,603 --> 00:14:59,189
Yes, his staff will contact you
regarding the project.

232
00:14:59,398 --> 00:15:01,358
-Please proceed with it.
-Yes, ma'am.

233
00:15:02,484 --> 00:15:04,612
How is the hearing
for the Minister of Justice going?

234
00:15:04,695 --> 00:15:08,032
It looks like Mr. Lee will go all out
against Mr. Song at the hearing.

235
00:15:08,115 --> 00:15:10,868
I heard he's focusing on
Mr. Song and Lee Chang-jin's relationship.

236
00:15:10,993 --> 00:15:13,704
Ms. Kang, if I may ask,

237
00:15:13,787 --> 00:15:16,123
are you planning
on helping Mr. Lee Seong-min?

238
00:15:16,707 --> 00:15:19,335
It will be too much for him
to prepare for the hearing alone.

239
00:15:19,418 --> 00:15:21,462
I'm just a bit concerned.

240
00:15:21,545 --> 00:15:25,007
I understand his circumstances,
but this seems a bit risky.

241
00:15:25,090 --> 00:15:29,261
I feel as if you're walking a thin line
between Mr. Song and Mr. Jo.

242
00:15:29,803 --> 00:15:30,763
I know.

243
00:15:30,846 --> 00:15:33,265
That's why I need your help,

244
00:15:33,349 --> 00:15:34,892
so I don't fall from it, Mr. Go.

245
00:15:34,975 --> 00:15:38,771
I don't know how I can be of help to you,
but I will do my best.

246
00:16:02,586 --> 00:16:03,837
Please buy me a meal.

247
00:16:16,517 --> 00:16:17,559
Did anything happen?

248
00:16:19,645 --> 00:16:20,688
No.

249
00:16:22,272 --> 00:16:24,608
I don't think you came to me
only for a meal.

250
00:16:24,692 --> 00:16:26,068
You can tell me.

251
00:16:32,574 --> 00:16:34,660
Give me a call if you need help.

252
00:16:40,499 --> 00:16:42,626
Please lend me some money.

253
00:16:44,211 --> 00:16:45,587
What is it for?

254
00:16:45,671 --> 00:16:47,631
Don't ask me that.
Just lend me some money.

255
00:16:47,715 --> 00:16:50,843
Out of everyone I know,
you're probably the richest lady.

256
00:16:53,846 --> 00:16:55,097
How much do you need?

257
00:16:56,390 --> 00:16:57,433
I need one million won.

258
00:16:59,852 --> 00:17:01,562
Why? Do you not have that much?

259
00:17:02,521 --> 00:17:03,605
By any chance,

260
00:17:05,357 --> 00:17:06,525
are you considering

261
00:17:07,943 --> 00:17:09,028
getting an abortion?

262
00:17:10,279 --> 00:17:12,781
Does the assistant administrator
know that you've come to meet me?

263
00:17:14,366 --> 00:17:16,118
Forget it if you don't want to.

264
00:17:18,912 --> 00:17:19,955
Su-min.

265
00:17:37,723 --> 00:17:39,558
Isn't she Su-min
from the lone-parent center?

266
00:17:40,017 --> 00:17:41,185
Why did she come to see you?

267
00:17:42,978 --> 00:17:45,564
It looks like she left the center.

268
00:17:47,524 --> 00:17:49,109
Could you look into it?

269
00:17:49,735 --> 00:17:50,694
Sure.

270
00:17:56,492 --> 00:17:58,952
ONE HEART PRINTING SERVICE

271
00:18:03,749 --> 00:18:04,792
Excuse me.

272
00:18:07,878 --> 00:18:08,921
Hello.

273
00:18:09,838 --> 00:18:12,674
-What brings you here?
-Mr. Oh Won-sik sent me on an errand here.

274
00:18:14,093 --> 00:18:16,386
Mr. Oh sent you here? Hold on.

275
00:18:22,768 --> 00:18:25,771
Tell him that I'd appreciate
his help next time too.

276
00:18:27,731 --> 00:18:29,566
-Thank you. Have a good day.
-Sure.

277
00:18:41,370 --> 00:18:42,913
We've been working in politics for long.

278
00:18:42,996 --> 00:18:45,290
And our districts are placed
right next to each other's.

279
00:18:45,374 --> 00:18:48,460
But we've been so distant to one another
for all this time.

280
00:18:49,169 --> 00:18:50,671
Please make this brief.

281
00:18:50,754 --> 00:18:53,966
I don't think we're close enough
to have a meal together.

282
00:18:55,217 --> 00:18:57,010
You're right. I'll get to the point.

283
00:18:57,594 --> 00:19:00,764
Seeing the path you've taken
as an assemblyman,

284
00:19:00,848 --> 00:19:03,725
there is a great number of things
I could learn from you.

285
00:19:03,892 --> 00:19:05,644
If everyone could work as hard as you do,

286
00:19:05,727 --> 00:19:08,480
our dear country
will be a much better one.

287
00:19:08,772 --> 00:19:11,608
But for you to handle all of your tasks,

288
00:19:12,317 --> 00:19:15,696
don't you think
that you'd need more than four years?

289
00:19:15,988 --> 00:19:18,282
Your term will mature next year.

290
00:19:18,365 --> 00:19:20,325
You must get reelected

291
00:19:20,409 --> 00:19:22,452
and continue to serve the country.

292
00:19:23,704 --> 00:19:25,122
What are you trying to say?

293
00:19:25,205 --> 00:19:26,415
At the last general election,

294
00:19:26,498 --> 00:19:27,875
the candidate of our party

295
00:19:27,958 --> 00:19:30,043
was disqualified
due to the corruption scandal,

296
00:19:30,127 --> 00:19:31,879
and you got lucky
and became an assemblyman.

297
00:19:32,254 --> 00:19:35,215
But I'm not sure if you'll have
such luck next year again.

298
00:19:35,299 --> 00:19:37,718
You're an independent assemblyman
without any support.

299
00:19:37,801 --> 00:19:40,012
The public support
continues to drop in your district.

300
00:19:40,095 --> 00:19:42,472
Given your situation,
do you think you can be reelected?

301
00:19:42,556 --> 00:19:45,601
So if you join our party...

302
00:19:45,684 --> 00:19:48,645
I wasn't aware that you were
concerned about my reelection.

303
00:19:49,354 --> 00:19:52,191
Mr. Lee, to serve a greater purpose
in our society,

304
00:19:52,274 --> 00:19:54,067
a little bit of compromise is necessary.

305
00:19:54,651 --> 00:19:55,986
"I'm getting into politics

306
00:19:56,069 --> 00:19:58,614
because I want to empower the powerless."

307
00:19:58,697 --> 00:20:00,407
That was

308
00:20:00,490 --> 00:20:03,243
one of your campaign promises
in the last general election.

309
00:20:03,327 --> 00:20:04,411
If you give up now,

310
00:20:04,494 --> 00:20:07,497
who is going to protect
all those people that voted for you?

311
00:20:08,165 --> 00:20:09,958
Or are you going to tell me

312
00:20:10,042 --> 00:20:12,252
that you were just bluffing
to win more votes?

313
00:20:13,670 --> 00:20:17,299
You see,
even water lilies are rooted in mud.

314
00:20:17,382 --> 00:20:18,884
A little bit of mud

315
00:20:18,967 --> 00:20:22,012
cannot mar
the graceful beauty of water lilies.

316
00:20:22,346 --> 00:20:24,514
The flower must bloom again next year,
you know.

317
00:20:27,684 --> 00:20:31,146
I won't bother trying to get reelected
if I must soil my hands and feet with mud.

318
00:20:32,648 --> 00:20:34,399
And by the same token,
I can't support you.

319
00:20:36,610 --> 00:20:37,861
I should get going.

320
00:20:44,576 --> 00:20:46,203
An assemblyman like him really exists?

321
00:20:46,870 --> 00:20:48,080
My goodness.

322
00:20:48,997 --> 00:20:50,707
I came to coax him, not to be insulted.

323
00:20:50,791 --> 00:20:54,461
That arrogant prick.
Look at him acting all upright and honest.

324
00:20:54,544 --> 00:20:56,880
I'll meet with Assemblyman Lee one-on-one.

325
00:20:57,464 --> 00:20:58,548
No, don't bother.

326
00:20:58,632 --> 00:21:00,884
Let Won-sik handle him.

327
00:21:01,760 --> 00:21:03,804
He won't lower his head.
Let's hit him in the neck

328
00:21:04,680 --> 00:21:06,807
to show him how cutthroat
those in politics can be.

329
00:21:13,855 --> 00:21:15,524
This is Yun Hye-won
from Mr. Song's office.

330
00:21:16,608 --> 00:21:19,778
Right, I'll resend the missing documents
for the hearing.

331
00:21:19,861 --> 00:21:21,571
-Da-jeong, did you check your e-mail?
-Okay.

332
00:21:21,655 --> 00:21:22,781
Yes, I did.

333
00:21:22,864 --> 00:21:25,117
Why are there
so many pre-hearing questionnaires?

334
00:21:25,200 --> 00:21:27,577
-I can't even take a break.
-Pass me those reports, Mr. Kim.

335
00:21:28,745 --> 00:21:29,705
I'm back.

336
00:21:31,581 --> 00:21:33,208
Did Mr. Oh step out or something?

337
00:21:33,709 --> 00:21:35,794
He's visiting the district office.

338
00:21:36,545 --> 00:21:37,546
Where have you been?

339
00:21:37,629 --> 00:21:40,424
I picked up the printed samples
of our policy handbook.

340
00:21:47,889 --> 00:21:50,267
Come over here and organize these reports
for each office.

341
00:21:50,350 --> 00:21:51,435
Sure.

342
00:21:56,857 --> 00:21:58,525
ONE HEART PRINTING SERVICE

343
00:22:00,986 --> 00:22:03,030
SEONGJIN CITY
DAEHAN PARTY COMMITTEE

344
00:22:03,613 --> 00:22:04,781
Sir!

345
00:22:05,615 --> 00:22:06,992
How have you been?

346
00:22:12,205 --> 00:22:14,082
I haven't seen you at all lately.

347
00:22:14,916 --> 00:22:16,001
What brings you here?

348
00:22:17,461 --> 00:22:21,340
This pleasant breeze made me think of you,
Mr. Assemblyman. Here.

349
00:22:21,423 --> 00:22:23,925
Assemblyman, my foot.
I took off my badge years ago.

350
00:22:24,009 --> 00:22:27,554
Losing the election once doesn't mean
you can never wear the badge again.

351
00:22:27,637 --> 00:22:29,848
What's this random blabbering about?

352
00:22:29,931 --> 00:22:32,309
I was told to oversee this district
because I lost.

353
00:22:32,392 --> 00:22:33,602
Assemblyman Song is ruthless.

354
00:22:33,685 --> 00:22:35,354
Giving you this position

355
00:22:35,437 --> 00:22:37,939
was his thoughtful decision
for next year's election.

356
00:22:40,984 --> 00:22:44,363
Sir, you should crush Lee Seong-min

357
00:22:44,446 --> 00:22:45,864
and make a comeback.

358
00:22:46,907 --> 00:22:48,241
Look at Seongjin City.

359
00:22:48,367 --> 00:22:51,370
It's become a hot mess
since that man got elected.

360
00:22:51,453 --> 00:22:54,414
He's even trying to cancel
the projects that you were working on.

361
00:22:54,581 --> 00:22:55,707
You need to get reelected

362
00:22:55,791 --> 00:22:58,794
to represent the city next year
and take good care of it.

363
00:22:58,877 --> 00:23:01,171
Let's be honest. Did he beat you last time

364
00:23:01,254 --> 00:23:02,881
because he's more competent than you are?

365
00:23:03,465 --> 00:23:04,758
He was just lucky.

366
00:23:04,841 --> 00:23:06,760
Why did the prosecution
investigate me right then?

367
00:23:06,885 --> 00:23:08,929
Who doesn't spend money during campaigns?

368
00:23:09,012 --> 00:23:10,180
Exactly.

369
00:23:13,350 --> 00:23:15,394
So? What are you trying to suggest?

370
00:23:15,477 --> 00:23:16,561
Listen.

371
00:23:22,067 --> 00:23:24,111
But if I step in, it won't look good.

372
00:23:24,194 --> 00:23:26,571
Of course,
you shouldn't get directly involved.

373
00:23:26,655 --> 00:23:27,948
FOR THE ORDINARY PEOPLE

374
00:23:28,031 --> 00:23:29,950
I was going through the list
of party members

375
00:23:30,033 --> 00:23:32,744
and found the right man for this.

376
00:23:32,953 --> 00:23:35,288
Do you remember that man
who helped you during your campaign?

377
00:23:35,372 --> 00:23:36,832
He was a CAO of a township.

378
00:23:37,249 --> 00:23:40,127
He's still a committed member
of our party.

379
00:23:40,877 --> 00:23:43,338
-He'd be perfect for the job.
-Yes.

380
00:23:43,422 --> 00:23:45,298
Give him any position,
and he'll do a great job.

381
00:23:46,925 --> 00:23:49,177
Will it really be okay though?
You know who he is.

382
00:23:49,261 --> 00:23:50,429
I sure do.

383
00:23:51,555 --> 00:23:54,599
And that's why he's perfect for the job.

384
00:23:56,393 --> 00:23:57,936
ASSEMBLYMAN SONG HUI-SEOP'S OFFICE

385
00:23:58,186 --> 00:24:00,313
Ms. Yun, we're heading out to eat.
Do you want to come?

386
00:24:00,480 --> 00:24:02,691
I'll eat in a bit. You guys go ahead.

387
00:24:04,609 --> 00:24:05,777
All right, then.

388
00:24:07,612 --> 00:24:08,864
What shall we eat?

389
00:24:09,656 --> 00:24:11,199
Whatever you like.

390
00:24:11,700 --> 00:24:14,077
I know of a great place.

391
00:24:18,290 --> 00:24:20,417
Ms. Yun, I'm stepping out for some food.

392
00:24:21,168 --> 00:24:23,420
Okay. Just a second, Da-jeong.

393
00:24:24,379 --> 00:24:26,756
-Yes?
-About our policy handbook...

394
00:24:26,840 --> 00:24:29,468
Did we send the print job
to One Heart Printing Service?

395
00:24:30,135 --> 00:24:34,514
-No, we use a different print shop.
-What about the district office's?

396
00:24:34,598 --> 00:24:37,058
Mr. Oh takes care
of all the print materials for them.

397
00:24:38,310 --> 00:24:40,395
Can I see the report Mr. Oh requested?

398
00:24:40,479 --> 00:24:43,523
The one on policy research
and development service.

399
00:24:44,566 --> 00:24:45,609
Sure.

400
00:24:49,279 --> 00:24:51,281
RESEARCH ON SEOBUK MARKET
AND REDEVELOPMENT PLANS

401
00:25:06,129 --> 00:25:07,881
Hello, this is One Heart Printing Service.

402
00:25:08,131 --> 00:25:10,008
Hello, this is Assemblyman Song's office.

403
00:25:11,259 --> 00:25:12,594
Right, yes.

404
00:25:15,597 --> 00:25:19,017
Mr. Oh wants to place a bookbinding order
for our policy handbook.

405
00:25:20,560 --> 00:25:23,188
Would 200 be enough, as usual?

406
00:25:25,398 --> 00:25:27,567
Sure. I'll send you the file via e-mail.

407
00:25:27,651 --> 00:25:29,736
Okay, great. Thank you.

408
00:25:33,156 --> 00:25:35,283
EXPENDITURE DETAILS

409
00:25:35,367 --> 00:25:37,619
2,000 COPIES

410
00:25:59,933 --> 00:26:01,226
Mr. Jang.

411
00:26:11,486 --> 00:26:12,779
The doors are opening.

412
00:26:21,621 --> 00:26:22,747
Mr. Jang.

413
00:26:24,457 --> 00:26:25,542
Well...

414
00:26:26,501 --> 00:26:29,796
I'm really sorry about yesterday.
I didn't know any better.

415
00:26:29,879 --> 00:26:32,257
I'll work harder from now on
and try to learn from you.

416
00:26:32,632 --> 00:26:34,050
You don't need to apologize.

417
00:26:35,135 --> 00:26:36,595
Everything you said is right.

418
00:26:38,096 --> 00:26:39,639
You want to be a chief of staff?

419
00:26:39,723 --> 00:26:41,266
Even so, you don't need to copy me.

420
00:26:41,349 --> 00:26:43,101
If you want to survive here,

421
00:26:43,184 --> 00:26:45,186
just act on your beliefs.

422
00:26:50,984 --> 00:26:52,110
I'll work hard.

423
00:26:58,617 --> 00:27:00,660
Did you gather
all the requested documents?

424
00:27:01,494 --> 00:27:02,537
No, not yet.

425
00:27:02,621 --> 00:27:04,998
Everyone on the committee
requested basic stuff,

426
00:27:05,081 --> 00:27:07,417
except for Mr. Lee Seong-min
who sent a lengthy list.

427
00:27:07,500 --> 00:27:09,711
He even contacted the prosecution
for case files

428
00:27:09,794 --> 00:27:11,713
from when Mr. Song was a prosecutor.

429
00:27:13,798 --> 00:27:16,051
He even requested those files?

430
00:27:17,052 --> 00:27:19,512
It looks like the prosecution
has already sent him a few things.

431
00:27:20,096 --> 00:27:23,642
Lee Seong-min can't analyze
the case reports on his own.

432
00:27:24,351 --> 00:27:25,894
I bet Kang Seon-yeong will help him.

433
00:27:27,312 --> 00:27:31,024
I guess she really plans
to play with a bigger fire.

434
00:27:38,907 --> 00:27:40,075
He requested all of that?

435
00:27:40,742 --> 00:27:43,787
I'll do my best to make sure
the sensitive stuff won't be disclosed.

436
00:27:45,080 --> 00:27:46,956
Just send everything over.

437
00:27:47,207 --> 00:27:48,917
He won't have time to read them anyway.

438
00:27:49,876 --> 00:27:50,752
What do you mean?

439
00:27:50,835 --> 00:27:53,672
Assemblyman Lee won't be able
to prepare for the hearing.

440
00:27:55,090 --> 00:27:56,216
With all that's going on,

441
00:27:56,299 --> 00:27:57,926
he won't even care about the hearing.

442
00:28:04,599 --> 00:28:06,976
I asked our party members in Seongjin City
for help.

443
00:28:07,060 --> 00:28:09,604
Hey, if Lee Seong-min finds out about it,

444
00:28:09,688 --> 00:28:11,815
-he won't let it slide.
-Gosh.

445
00:28:12,649 --> 00:28:13,525
Don't worry, sir.

446
00:28:13,608 --> 00:28:15,568
I hired someone

447
00:28:15,652 --> 00:28:18,238
whom even Lee Seong-min can't ignore.

448
00:28:21,282 --> 00:28:23,076
When Mr. Song was a prosecutor,

449
00:28:23,159 --> 00:28:25,954
he worked on five cases
related to Lee Chang-jin.

450
00:28:26,037 --> 00:28:28,957
Then shouldn't we bring him in
as a witness?

451
00:28:29,040 --> 00:28:31,835
Both the ruling and opposition parties
will have to agree on it,

452
00:28:31,918 --> 00:28:34,421
including Mr. No of the opposition party,
Mr. Ahn of our party,

453
00:28:34,504 --> 00:28:36,423
and the chairperson
of the Judiciary Committee.

454
00:28:36,506 --> 00:28:37,841
They all support Mr. Song.

455
00:28:41,386 --> 00:28:44,347
Let's request additional documents
to strengthen our case.

456
00:28:44,764 --> 00:28:46,975
-Okay.
-Where is Assemblyman Lee Seong-min?

457
00:28:47,058 --> 00:28:48,560
-Where is he hiding?
-Where is he?

458
00:28:48,643 --> 00:28:50,687
-Can I help you?
-Move! You're not him.

459
00:28:50,770 --> 00:28:51,980
You can't go in.

460
00:28:52,063 --> 00:28:54,315
Step aside.
I told you that I have to meet him.

461
00:28:54,399 --> 00:28:55,400
-Please wait--
-Move!

462
00:28:55,483 --> 00:28:57,277
What? We've been waiting all this time!

463
00:28:57,360 --> 00:28:59,362
-Stop bullshitting us.
-Tell him to come out!

464
00:28:59,446 --> 00:29:00,613
-Come out!
-You can't...

465
00:29:02,157 --> 00:29:04,117
The redevelopment was decided long ago.

466
00:29:04,200 --> 00:29:05,785
How could you try to stop it now?

467
00:29:05,869 --> 00:29:09,038
-It's ridiculous.
-Hundreds of people agreed on it, okay?

468
00:29:09,122 --> 00:29:11,082
I voted for you because of my son.

469
00:29:11,166 --> 00:29:12,542
What the hell is this about?

470
00:29:12,625 --> 00:29:14,836
Sir, please calm down.

471
00:29:14,919 --> 00:29:18,173
Please wait until we sort things out
with the merchants.

472
00:29:18,256 --> 00:29:20,425
They have nowhere to go.
They're struggling, you know.

473
00:29:20,508 --> 00:29:22,969
Are you saying we, the landlords,
aren't struggling?

474
00:29:23,052 --> 00:29:25,513
-That's right!
-After being renters for years,

475
00:29:25,597 --> 00:29:27,307
we saved up and bought our properties.

476
00:29:27,390 --> 00:29:29,100
-Yes!
-Exactly!

477
00:29:29,184 --> 00:29:31,644
If a small piece of land
and a home are all we own,

478
00:29:31,728 --> 00:29:34,105
-we're also considered the working class.
-Yes, absolutely!

479
00:29:34,189 --> 00:29:36,399
-Cut it out!
-Please hear me out first.

480
00:29:36,483 --> 00:29:38,151
We don't need to hear your bullshit!

481
00:29:38,234 --> 00:29:40,403
We won't even take a step
out of this place

482
00:29:40,487 --> 00:29:42,864
until the construction resumes,
so consider yourself informed.

483
00:29:42,947 --> 00:29:44,240
-Yes!
-We won't even budge.

484
00:29:44,741 --> 00:29:45,742
-Everyone, sit down!
-Okay.

485
00:29:45,825 --> 00:29:47,827
-Let's all sit down!
-Sit.

486
00:29:47,911 --> 00:29:50,038
-Goodness.
-You can't do this here.

487
00:29:50,789 --> 00:29:52,248
Sir, you can't be doing this here.

488
00:29:56,252 --> 00:29:58,171
-Oh, my goodness.
-There are cameras here.

489
00:29:59,422 --> 00:30:00,381
-My gosh...
-Oh, no!

490
00:30:02,300 --> 00:30:03,760
-Everyone, leave.
-No photos, please.

491
00:30:03,885 --> 00:30:06,054
-My gosh.
-Are you all right?

492
00:30:06,137 --> 00:30:07,472
-Please leave.
-Goodness.

493
00:30:07,555 --> 00:30:09,516
-How could an assemblyman...
-Is he a thug or what?

494
00:30:10,225 --> 00:30:12,769
-Assemblyman Lee Seong-min hit me!
-Gosh.

495
00:30:12,852 --> 00:30:14,229
-Call security.
-Call them.

496
00:30:14,312 --> 00:30:16,481
-In an assemblyman's office...
-This is crazy.

497
00:30:17,065 --> 00:30:18,691
-We're here to submit a complaint.
-Look.

498
00:30:19,067 --> 00:30:21,069
-I won't even budge.
-We need a solution.

499
00:30:21,152 --> 00:30:23,279
-You saw he hit me.
-My gosh.

500
00:30:23,780 --> 00:30:25,406
-Oh, boy. My goodness...
-Excuse me.

501
00:30:25,573 --> 00:30:27,033
Ouch, my back.

502
00:30:27,116 --> 00:30:28,368
Make way for him.

503
00:30:29,911 --> 00:30:30,829
Dad!

