But they didn't give us the case materials

756
00:50:56,553 --> 00:50:58,680
saying there were no records
since it happened long ago.

757
00:50:58,764 --> 00:51:01,016
After Mr. Sung became
the honorary chairman,

758
00:51:01,099 --> 00:51:02,809
there was an issue
with his inheritance tax.

759
00:51:02,893 --> 00:51:06,813
And that's when the FSS checked
all his borrowed-name bank accounts.

760
00:51:06,897 --> 00:51:10,025
Mr. Song definitely would've
received some money from him.

761
00:51:10,108 --> 00:51:12,611
Mr. Song can stop the prosecution
from handing over any materials,

762
00:51:12,694 --> 00:51:14,654
but not the FSS.

763
00:51:15,781 --> 00:51:16,782
We'll need help

764
00:51:16,865 --> 00:51:20,452
from other assembly members
to dig into something this big.

765
00:51:20,535 --> 00:51:23,705
But they're all very cautious
because Mr. Song is currently in office.

766
00:51:23,789 --> 00:51:25,123
If we raise suspicions,

767
00:51:25,207 --> 00:51:27,626
they won't be able to stand still.

768
00:51:28,668 --> 00:51:29,878
Let's start out with the press.

769
00:51:34,674 --> 00:51:36,176
Are we done with
the opposition party's questionnaires?

770
00:51:36,259 --> 00:51:39,304
We're only left with additional
questionnaires from Mr. Jang and Mr. Lee.

771
00:51:39,387 --> 00:51:41,681
Give me Mr. Lee's questionnaire.

772
00:51:42,474 --> 00:51:43,767
Here.

773
00:51:48,688 --> 00:51:50,398
Have some coffee, everyone.

774
00:51:50,899 --> 00:51:52,526
I really needed some coffee.

775
00:51:56,196 --> 00:51:57,030
Thanks.

776
00:52:00,158 --> 00:52:01,159
Mr. Jang.

777
00:52:01,743 --> 00:52:02,994
Take a short break.

778
00:52:03,078 --> 00:52:04,746
-Thanks.
-Sure.

779
00:52:07,040 --> 00:52:08,125
This is so nice.

780
00:52:08,625 --> 00:52:10,919
My gosh, it's nice and refreshing.

781
00:52:11,503 --> 00:52:12,629
Next on the news.

782
00:52:13,171 --> 00:52:14,214
The hearing for the nominee

783
00:52:14,297 --> 00:52:15,924
for the Minister of Justice
is in two days.

784
00:52:16,007 --> 00:52:19,094
And suspicions regarding Assemblyman Song
have started to arise.

785
00:52:19,177 --> 00:52:22,139
Assemblyman Lee requested the FSS
for files regarding the Youngil Group case

786
00:52:22,222 --> 00:52:25,642
saying Assemblyman Song might've been
lenient with the company

787
00:52:25,725 --> 00:52:28,645
back when he was in charge
of the company's slush fund case.

788
00:52:28,728 --> 00:52:31,606
The opposition party has decided
to start an investigation into it,

789
00:52:31,690 --> 00:52:34,776
and this could cause some trouble
during the upcoming hearing.

790
00:52:34,860 --> 00:52:36,194
Call the FSS and get the files.

791
00:52:36,778 --> 00:52:38,238
-Okay.
-Okay.

792
00:52:49,708 --> 00:52:51,793
Is there anything I should know
about Youngil Group?

793
00:52:51,877 --> 00:52:54,504
No, you don't need to worry
about anything.

794
00:52:54,588 --> 00:52:57,340
They're causing a fuss over something
that happened so long ago.

795
00:52:57,424 --> 00:52:59,050
They're now trying to put me in trouble

796
00:52:59,134 --> 00:53:01,469
because they couldn't find anything
I did wrong.

797
00:53:01,553 --> 00:53:03,763
Sir, I need to know
in order to prepare for the hearing.

798
00:53:03,847 --> 00:53:05,891
How far were you involved in the case?

799
00:53:05,974 --> 00:53:07,058
I told you not to worry!

800
00:53:07,684 --> 00:53:09,686
You don't need to worry
about anything else.

801
00:53:09,769 --> 00:53:11,605
Just focus on preparing for the hearing.

802
00:53:24,868 --> 00:53:25,994
See you later, sir.

803
00:53:32,083 --> 00:53:33,418
Did you call the FSS?

804
00:53:34,628 --> 00:53:37,047
They already sent the files
to Mr. Lee's office.

805
00:53:37,130 --> 00:53:38,882
They agreed to send us the files as well.

806
00:53:38,965 --> 00:53:40,967
But those files are the results
of the investigation

807
00:53:41,051 --> 00:53:43,261
into Youngil Group's
borrowed-name accounts.

808
00:53:43,345 --> 00:53:46,223
If there's any evidence that shows
that Mr. Song received money from them,

809
00:53:46,306 --> 00:53:47,766
it'll give him a fatal blow.

810
00:53:59,861 --> 00:54:01,112
COURIER SERVICE

811
00:54:06,117 --> 00:54:07,118
Hey, it's me.

812
00:54:08,203 --> 00:54:09,496
I have a favor to ask.

813
00:54:11,414 --> 00:54:13,500
If they trace Youngil Group's money,

814
00:54:13,583 --> 00:54:16,002
they'll find out where Samil Association
gets the funding.

815
00:54:16,086 --> 00:54:18,505
Sir, do you have any way to stop this?

816
00:54:18,588 --> 00:54:20,674
Everyone has a right to speak,

817
00:54:20,757 --> 00:54:24,261
so I can't stop Mr. Lee Seong-min from
talking just because I'm the chairperson.

818
00:54:24,344 --> 00:54:25,804
Darn it.

819
00:54:26,429 --> 00:54:29,724
I'm more than glad to have our member
become the Minister of Justice,

820
00:54:29,808 --> 00:54:31,393
but this is way too risky.

821
00:54:34,813 --> 00:54:36,606
We'll end up losing a lot more

822
00:54:36,690 --> 00:54:39,025
than what we gain.

823
00:54:43,154 --> 00:54:45,907
If Youngil Group becomes a public issue,

824
00:54:46,449 --> 00:54:48,660
Chairman Sung won't stand still.

825
00:54:53,873 --> 00:54:55,333
-Goodbye.
-Goodbye.

826
00:54:55,417 --> 00:54:56,293
Goodbye, sir.

827
00:54:57,585 --> 00:54:58,712
Goodbye, sir.

828
00:55:06,428 --> 00:55:08,054
Chairman Sung is currently abroad.

829
00:55:08,138 --> 00:55:10,265
I'm not sure
if I should report to him about this.

830
00:55:10,348 --> 00:55:12,100
This is quite a tough situation.

831
00:55:14,519 --> 00:55:15,937
I'll take care of it.

832
00:55:16,021 --> 00:55:17,272
So just stay quiet.

833
00:55:17,856 --> 00:55:19,816
Do you have a good idea?

834
00:55:25,613 --> 00:55:28,033
Are you thinking about using Jang Tae-jun?

835
00:55:33,330 --> 00:55:35,915
My goodness.
It's going to be a waste to lose him,

836
00:55:35,999 --> 00:55:38,168
but at least it'll help us
get out of trouble.

837
00:55:38,251 --> 00:55:40,670
Did you purposely make him
take care of all your mess until now

838
00:55:40,754 --> 00:55:42,213
so you could use him like this?

839
00:55:42,797 --> 00:55:46,676
My goodness.
You're a very scary man, Mr. Song.

840
00:55:48,303 --> 00:55:50,013
-Mr. Lee.
-Yes?

841
00:55:50,597 --> 00:55:54,100
By any chance,
does Tae-jun have anything on you?

842
00:55:55,602 --> 00:55:58,188
Well, I wouldn't exactly put it like that.

843
00:55:59,522 --> 00:56:00,899
But I found out

844
00:56:02,067 --> 00:56:04,235
that he's a very ambitious man.

845
00:56:11,409 --> 00:56:14,454
I'm sure you didn't come empty-handed
to settle a deal.

846
00:56:14,537 --> 00:56:15,747
So tell me.

847
00:56:16,331 --> 00:56:17,749
Let's hear what you have to say.

848
00:56:17,832 --> 00:56:19,542
In order to become the minister,

849
00:56:19,626 --> 00:56:20,919
you'll have no choice

850
00:56:21,002 --> 00:56:23,380
but to hand over the floor leader position
to Chairperson Lee.

851
00:56:23,463 --> 00:56:25,131
What will you be offering me?

852
00:56:26,633 --> 00:56:28,385
You know
the Minister of Justice has authority

853
00:56:28,468 --> 00:56:30,387
over the prosecution's
personnel matters, right?

854
00:56:30,470 --> 00:56:32,847
There are way too many positions
to fill the organization

855
00:56:32,931 --> 00:56:35,183
with just my people alone.

856
00:56:39,437 --> 00:56:41,856
Are you sure there will be
a position for me?

857
00:56:41,940 --> 00:56:44,109
You can turn down the offer
if you don't like it.

858
00:56:47,028 --> 00:56:48,988
But you see, you need

859
00:56:49,072 --> 00:56:52,492
to become the Minister of Justice first
in order for this deal to be valid.

860
00:56:52,575 --> 00:56:55,537
How are you going to deal with the issue
regarding Youngil Group?

861
00:56:55,745 --> 00:56:57,580
They're doing everything
they can to hurt me,

862
00:56:57,831 --> 00:57:02,001
so I'll have to let them
bite off my arm if that's necessary.

863
00:57:08,883 --> 00:57:11,886
Are you okay with losing someone
that's so good at his job?

864
00:57:11,970 --> 00:57:14,305
What's the use of keeping a cow
that's done doing its job?

865
00:57:14,889 --> 00:57:16,433
It'll only cost me money to feed it.

866
00:57:16,516 --> 00:57:19,144
Now, it's time to butcher and eat the cow.

867
00:57:30,071 --> 00:57:32,240
HANSUNG LAUNDRY

868
00:57:47,922 --> 00:57:48,923
My goodness.

869
00:57:49,007 --> 00:57:51,426
I was just getting ready to close.

870
00:57:52,427 --> 00:57:54,429
Are you here to have it dry-cleaned?

871
00:57:58,475 --> 00:58:01,394
-Mom, is it this one?
-I told you there's one that's washed.

872
00:58:01,478 --> 00:58:02,854
Why did you bring out a new one?

873
00:58:05,982 --> 00:58:06,816
Ms. Yun.

874
00:58:19,704 --> 00:58:21,581
You forgot to take these,
so I brought them.

875
00:58:22,373 --> 00:58:23,458
Thank you.

876
00:58:26,294 --> 00:58:28,922
PERSONNEL RECORD
HAN DO-GYEONG

877
00:58:32,300 --> 00:58:33,384
What are you planning to do?

878
00:58:36,971 --> 00:58:37,931
I'm going to study

879
00:58:38,932 --> 00:58:40,391
for the civil service exam again.

880
00:58:43,728 --> 00:58:45,980
Didn't you say you wanted
to become a chief of staff?

881
00:58:54,197 --> 00:58:55,698
You once asked me

882
00:58:58,284 --> 00:59:00,703
why I started working here.

883
00:59:01,788 --> 00:59:03,373
DODAM DAILY
YUN HYE-WON

884
00:59:07,126 --> 00:59:08,711
EXCLUSIVE

885
00:59:10,463 --> 00:59:11,673
DODAM DAILY
REPORTER YUN HYE-WON

886
00:59:11,756 --> 00:59:13,424
HANJANG CONSTRUCTIONS, SUSPICIONS ARISE...

887
00:59:13,508 --> 00:59:15,802
SHIN JAE-GYEONG RAISED SAFETY ISSUES
BUT WAS COMPLETELY IGNORED

888
00:59:22,517 --> 00:59:24,686
Hye-won, wait.

889
00:59:25,979 --> 00:59:28,106
You told me
you won't disclose Mr. Shin's identity.

890
00:59:28,189 --> 00:59:29,774
How could you disclose his name?

891
00:59:29,857 --> 00:59:32,360
You promised to protect his identity.

892
00:59:32,443 --> 00:59:34,195
That gives us no public confidence.

893
00:59:34,279 --> 00:59:36,072
We had to reveal his identity
for the article.

894
00:59:36,155 --> 00:59:37,407
Then what about Mr. Shin?

895
00:59:37,490 --> 00:59:38,658
He had faith in me!

896
00:59:38,741 --> 00:59:42,036
What's important is the article,
not the whistleblower!

897
00:59:50,420 --> 00:59:51,796
What happened?

898
00:59:52,338 --> 00:59:53,339
Next on the news.

899
00:59:53,423 --> 00:59:57,093
Mr. Shin, the whistleblower
of Hanjang Constructions' blueprint edits,

900
00:59:57,176 --> 00:59:59,178
tried to commit suicide.

901
00:59:59,262 --> 01:00:02,181
He was taken to the hospital
after having tried to commit suicide

902
01:00:02,265 --> 01:00:05,184
by burning charcoal in his car
early this morning.

903
01:00:05,268 --> 01:00:07,520
And he is currently
lying in the hospital unconscious.

904
01:00:07,604 --> 01:00:10,106
Mr. Shin, who used to work
at Hanjang Constructions,

905
01:00:10,189 --> 01:00:12,775
found out about the company's irregularity
and reported it

906
01:00:12,859 --> 01:00:14,319
to the press for the public good.

907
01:00:14,402 --> 01:00:17,280
However, once his identity got revealed,
he was pressured by the company,

908
01:00:17,363 --> 01:00:18,281
and his colleagues...

909
01:00:18,364 --> 01:00:19,907
I thought I'd be able

910
01:00:19,991 --> 01:00:22,118
to become the eyes and ears of the weak

911
01:00:22,201 --> 01:00:24,829
once I became a reporter.

912
01:00:26,497 --> 01:00:27,665
But

913
01:00:27,749 --> 01:00:30,752
there was absolutely nothing I could do.

914
01:00:31,878 --> 01:00:34,589
I couldn't even protect the person
who trusted me

915
01:00:34,672 --> 01:00:36,507
and told me everything.

916
01:00:38,635 --> 01:00:40,136
So I felt helpless.

917
01:00:40,887 --> 01:00:44,098
I may not be able to protect anyone,

918
01:00:44,891 --> 01:00:47,852
but I felt like I should at least try
to make the world a better place

919
01:00:48,478 --> 01:00:50,438
where people don't need such protection.

920
01:00:50,521 --> 01:00:52,440
That's why I started doing this job.

921
01:00:53,733 --> 01:00:55,318
Don't give up.

922
01:00:55,401 --> 01:00:56,819
Mr. Han,

923
01:00:57,487 --> 01:01:01,366
you must work in this field
for the sake of Yu Jin-su's grandmother.

924
01:01:02,283 --> 01:01:05,078
And it doesn't have
to be at Mr. Song's office.

925
01:01:06,120 --> 01:01:08,456
As long as you stick to your beliefs,

926
01:01:08,790 --> 01:01:12,085
I'm sure you'll find a place to work.

927
01:01:24,347 --> 01:01:25,348
I'll be off now.

928
01:01:42,907 --> 01:01:44,826
Mr. Jang, aren't you tired?

929
01:01:44,909 --> 01:01:46,244
My gosh.

930
01:01:46,911 --> 01:01:48,037
Good work.

931
01:01:48,121 --> 01:01:50,164
Thank you. You too, sir.

932
01:01:55,128 --> 01:01:56,170
Mr. Jang.

933
01:02:02,552 --> 01:02:03,928
What do you mean?

934
01:02:05,847 --> 01:02:07,056
You've done enough.

935
01:02:07,140 --> 01:02:10,476
I want you to stop
helping Mr. Lee Seong-min.

936
01:02:10,560 --> 01:02:13,229
I thought you were also against

937
01:02:13,312 --> 01:02:16,149
Mr. Song becoming the Minister of Justice.

938
01:02:16,691 --> 01:02:19,736
When the game changes,
I should change the way I think.

939
01:02:20,611 --> 01:02:24,282
Joojin Chemical's CEO will be
attending Assemblyman Song's hearing today

940
01:02:24,365 --> 01:02:27,452
as a witness regarding Assemblyman Song's
candidacy for the Minister of Justice.

941
01:02:27,535 --> 01:02:30,538
Both the ruling and opposition party
have come to an agreement

942
01:02:30,621 --> 01:02:34,333
and picked the witness to resolve
the suspicions regarding Assemblyman Song.

943
01:02:35,209 --> 01:02:36,627
Ms. Kang.

944
01:02:38,463 --> 01:02:41,716
Did you hear that Lee Chang-jin will be
attending the hearing as a witness?

945
01:02:42,425 --> 01:02:44,761
-Yes.
-Things aren't going the way we planned.

946
01:02:44,844 --> 01:02:46,262
Take a look at this.

947
01:03:04,030 --> 01:03:05,740
-He's here.
-Come on!

948
01:03:05,823 --> 01:03:07,950
-Sir!
-This is your first confirmation hearing.

949
01:03:08,034 --> 01:03:09,827
-Tell us how you feel.
-How do you feel?

950
01:03:09,911 --> 01:03:11,746
-Did both parties agree on...
-Sir.

951
01:03:11,913 --> 01:03:13,456
-Tell us how you feel.
-How do you feel?

952
01:03:13,623 --> 01:03:15,333
-Are you prepared?
-You're smiling.

953
01:03:15,416 --> 01:03:18,586
-Sir, please give us a word.
-Please tell us how you feel.

954
01:03:18,669 --> 01:03:21,422
-Sir, how do you feel?
-Please tell us how you feel.

955
01:03:21,506 --> 01:03:23,299
-Sir!
-Sir, please!

956
01:03:23,382 --> 01:03:24,884
Please tell us how you feel.

957
01:03:24,967 --> 01:03:27,929
Mr. Song, how did Lee Chang-jin end up
getting chosen as a witness?

958
01:03:28,012 --> 01:03:31,307
The opposition party and Lee Seong-min
kept causing a fuss,

959
01:03:31,390 --> 01:03:32,767
so I had no choice.

960
01:03:33,893 --> 01:03:35,061
It's actually for the better.

961
01:03:35,144 --> 01:03:37,772
I can use this chance
to resolve all the suspicions.

962
01:03:37,855 --> 01:03:39,482
-It won't be that bad.
-But sir...

963
01:03:40,691 --> 01:03:41,692
Is that the answer sheet?

964
01:03:42,401 --> 01:03:43,569
Yes, sir.

965
01:03:45,905 --> 01:03:49,242
Don't worry.
He won't say anything unnecessary.

966
01:04:07,343 --> 01:04:08,302
What is it?

967
01:04:08,386 --> 01:04:09,679
I don't have time to chat.

968
01:04:09,762 --> 01:04:12,473
Tae-jun, how far are you involved
with Mr. Lee Chang-jin?

969
01:04:14,433 --> 01:04:16,018
Let's talk about this next time.

970
01:04:16,602 --> 01:04:17,520
We need to talk now.

971
01:04:19,230 --> 01:04:21,107
Tell me what kind of deal
you had with him.

972
01:04:23,442 --> 01:04:25,945
There's a copy of the CCTV footage.

973
01:04:26,028 --> 01:04:27,530
Where is the copy?

974
01:04:27,613 --> 01:04:28,698
I have it.

975
01:04:28,781 --> 01:04:30,783
I'll give it to you

976
01:04:32,660 --> 01:04:34,036
when I join the National Assembly.

977
01:04:37,456 --> 01:04:39,250
I've already told you everything.

978
01:04:44,297 --> 01:04:46,048
It's the questionnaire
from Mr. Ahn's office.

979
01:04:46,132 --> 01:04:47,967
Read what's written on it.

980
01:04:48,551 --> 01:04:49,844
MR. SONG, ARE YOU AWARE

981
01:04:49,927 --> 01:04:52,096
MR. JANG USED YOUR AUTHORITY
TO THREATEN MR. LEE CHANG-JIN?

982
01:04:54,140 --> 01:04:56,183
Mr. Ahn is one of Mr. Song's closest men.

983
01:04:56,267 --> 01:04:59,478
He wouldn't have added this question
without discussing it with Mr. Song.

984
01:04:59,645 --> 01:05:01,439
Your name is being mentioned here.

985
01:05:01,522 --> 01:05:03,774
It's weird enough
that Mr. Lee got picked as a witness.

986
01:05:03,858 --> 01:05:06,777
They're trying to blame you
for all the suspicions regarding Mr. Song.

987
01:05:07,653 --> 01:05:11,115
They're going to make it
look like it was all your doing.

988
01:05:13,075 --> 01:05:14,577
We will now begin

989
01:05:14,660 --> 01:05:16,787
the hearing for the nominee
for the Minister of Justice

990
01:05:16,871 --> 01:05:21,042
based on Article 65, Clause 2
of the National Assembly Act and Article 4

991
01:05:21,125 --> 01:05:23,586
of the Personnel Hearing Act.

992
01:05:24,545 --> 01:05:25,588
CABINET MEMBER NOMINEE

993
01:05:25,671 --> 01:05:28,758
During my 20 years as a prosecutor,

994
01:05:28,841 --> 01:05:30,134
I felt rewarded that I was able

995
01:05:30,217 --> 01:05:32,261
to fight against injustice

996
01:05:32,386 --> 01:05:34,513
and take care of people who had to suffer.

997
01:05:34,597 --> 01:05:36,974
And during the past 10 years
as an assemblyman,

998
01:05:37,058 --> 01:05:39,435
I stuck by my belief and worked very hard

999
01:05:39,518 --> 01:05:43,230
to protect liberal democracy
and bring order and righteousness

1000
01:05:43,314 --> 01:05:45,566
to our national law.

1001
01:05:46,067 --> 01:05:47,234
If this question gets asked,

1002
01:05:47,318 --> 01:05:49,779
Mr. Song will only be left
with one choice.

1003
01:05:49,862 --> 01:05:51,405
He'll discard me.

1004
01:05:52,323 --> 01:05:54,909
The people of our country
have constantly been disappointed

1005
01:05:54,992 --> 01:05:57,912
because of the Ministry of Justice
and the prosecution.

1006
01:05:57,995 --> 01:06:01,457
And I'm very well aware
that they're seeking for a reformation

1007
01:06:01,540 --> 01:06:04,710
within the Ministry of Justice
and the prosecution.

1008
01:06:04,794 --> 01:06:07,171
Thus, I believe the Ministry of Justice
and the prosecution

1009
01:06:07,254 --> 01:06:10,758
-must look back on their faults
-What a smooth talker.

1010
01:06:10,841 --> 01:06:14,804
and be determined to change
and start anew.

1011
01:06:15,388 --> 01:06:17,932
If I become the Minister of Justice,

1012
01:06:18,307 --> 01:06:22,853
I will make sure the Ministry of Justice
becomes an organization that is just.

1013
01:06:23,437 --> 01:06:27,566
If I'm given the opportunity
to serve as the Minister of Justice,

1014
01:06:27,775 --> 01:06:30,736
I will work hard to serve my country
and its people

1015
01:06:30,820 --> 01:06:33,197
in the best way that I can.

1016
01:06:34,198 --> 01:06:35,199
Thank you.

1017
01:07:09,025 --> 01:07:11,527
Even a tiger eats its own cub
if it's cornered.

1018
01:07:11,610 --> 01:07:12,903
He's trying to put all the blame on me.

1019
01:07:12,987 --> 01:07:15,656
He was planning
to pin everything on Tae-jun.

1020
01:07:15,740 --> 01:07:17,867
The authority has put out an APB
on Mr. Jang.

1021
01:07:17,950 --> 01:07:19,785
We won't be able to save Tae-jun.

1022
01:07:19,869 --> 01:07:22,163
Let's stop here.
He's too big of a fish for us to catch.

1023
01:07:22,663 --> 01:07:24,999
-Let's start with this.
-Let's try everything we can.

1024
01:07:25,082 --> 01:07:27,668
Find Jang Tae-jun
and bring him to me right now!

1025
01:07:27,752 --> 01:07:29,587
Will Mr. Song let you?

1026
01:07:29,670 --> 01:07:32,923
I'll show you what happens

1027
01:07:33,007 --> 01:07:34,300
when you treat me with arrogance.

1028
01:07:34,383 --> 01:07:37,053
I'll bite off the tiger's neck
if I have to.

1029
01:07:59,575 --> 01:08:01,202
